commit.message: Move volatile to regular requirements
Move check_copyright to its own script

Switch to regular mypy.

I don't know the full story on mypy vs mypy-mypyc, but regular mypy
works with modern typed-ast that black depends on.  Before this change,
there's an unsatisfiable constraint for typed-ast.
Force in_process when using Windows

Switch from tempfile to volatile.

This is a wrapper around tempfile that lets us close it without
deleting.
Enable CI on windows and tmp-* branches

Switch to using moreorless for patching

This should be pretty close to working on windows when using
in_process=True now.
Fix encapsulate method in Query class
Use Github Actions badge in readme
Use codecov badge in readme
